{{more footnotes|date=July 2014}} {{Infobox saint | name = Abraham of Paleostrov | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | titles = Saint | birth_date = ''?'' | birth_place = | death_date = {{circa}} 460 | death_place = island of Paley, [[Lake Onega]] | venerated_in = Karelian and Novgorod Synaxis | beatified_date = | beatified_place = | beatified_by = | canonized_date = 19th century | canonized_place = | canonized_by = Archbishop Sergius (Spassky) | major_shrine = | feast_day = August 21 (September 3) | attributes = | patronage = | issues = | suppressed_date = | suppressed_by = | quote = }}
'''Abraham of Paleostrov''' ({{lang-ru|Авраамий Палеостровский}} - '''Avraamy Paleostrovsky'''; died c. 1460), '''Avraamy Olonetsky''' is a [[List of Russian saints (until 15th century)|saint in the Russian Orthodox Church]], a [[hegumen]] of [[Nativity of Mary|Nativity of the Blessed Virgin Mary]] monastery in Paleostrov. Abraham was a disciple of [[Cornelius of Paleostrov]] and one of his successors as [[abbot]] of his monastery.
==Life and ministration== From the ''Legend of the Life of the Reverend Cornelius of Paleostrov'', it is known that Abraham came to Cornelius after he had settled in a cave on the island of Paley on [[Lake Onega]]. The Paleostrovsky Monastery was founded by Cornelius, presumably no later than 1415-1421. Abraham together with other disciples of Cornelius participated in the construction of the churches of the [[Nativity of Mary|Nativity of the Blessed Virgin]], of [[Elijah|Elijah the Prophet]] and [[Saint Nicholas|Nikolaos the Wonderworker]], the caves for the monks. In the lifetime of Cornelius he appointed Abraham as his successor. The Venerable Cornelius died about 1420, Abraham buried him in the cave of the island of Paley. [[The Reverend]] Cornelius died about 1420, Abraham buried him in the cave of the island of Paley. Later, the relics of Cornelius Paleostrovsky were transferred to the Church of [[Nativity of Mary|Nativity of the Blessed Virgin]]. The Monk Abraham died in the middle of the 15th century. He was buried in the Church of the Nativity of the Virgin near Cornelius.<ref name="pravenc"/>
==Veneration== The date of the local canonization of Abraham Paleostrovsky is unknown. In the XVII century, the Palaeostrovsky Monastery was twice devastated, as a result of which most of the archive was lost. The local veneration of Abraham and Cornelius was documented at the beginning of the 19th century. Archbishop Sergius (Spassky) assigned the feast day of both saints - August 21. In 1974, Abraham Paleostrovsky was included in the Synaxis of the [[Karelia]]n Saints, and in 1981 - in the Synaxis of the [[Veliky Novgorod|Novgorod]] Saints.<ref name="pravenc">[http://www.pravenc.ru/text/73419.html/ АВРААМИЙ ПАЛЕОСТРОВСКИЙ] Retrieved on 12 Mar 2018</ref>
His [[feast day]] is celebrated on August 21 in the Russian church.<ref name="Synaxis of All Saints of Karelia">Synaxis of All Saints of Karelia</ref><ref>Synaxis of All Saints of Novgorod</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pravenc.ru/text/73419.html|script-title=ru:Авраамий Палеостровский|trans-title=Eleazar, Nazarius and Eumenius|publisher=Православная Энциклопедиа (The Orthodox Encyclopedia)|language=Russian}}</ref>
