{{for|the American pop singer|Jo Ann Campbell}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}} {{Use British English|date=January 2014}} {{Infobox person | name = Joanne Campbell | image = | imagesize = 180px | caption = | birthname = Joanne E Campbell<ref>[http://search.ancestry.co.uk/cgi-bin/sse.dll?MS_AdvCB=1&gl=ROOT_CATEGORY&rank=1&new=1&so=3&MSAV=1&msT=0&gss=ms_r_f-2&gsfn=joanne&gsfn_x=1&gsln=campbell&gsln_x=y1&rg_81004010__date=1964&81004010__date_x=1&msbpn__ftp=Northampton&msbpn_x=1&msbpn__ftp_x=1&msrpn_x=1&msrpn__ftp_x=1&81004030__date_x=1&msdpn_x=1&msdpn__ftp_x=1&_8000C000_x=1&_80008000_x=1&_80018000_x=1&_80014000_x=1&_80010000_x=1&81004200__date_x=1&_82004200-gpid_x=1&_82004200__ftp_x=1&81004210__date_x=1&_82004210-gpid_x=1&_82004210__ftp_x=1&_82004280-gpid_x=1&_82004280__ftp_x=1&_82004290-gpid_x=1&_82004290__ftp_x=1&81004240__date_x=1&_82004240-gpid_x=1&_82004240__ftp_x=1&81004020__date_x=1&_82004020-gpid_x=1&_82004020__ftp_x=1&81004230__date_x=1&_82004230-gpid_x=1&_82004230__ftp_x=1&gskw_x=1&_83004002_x=1&81000000__date_x=1&_82000000-gpid_x=1&_82000000__ftp_x=1&810002A0__date_x=1&_820002A0-gpid_x=1&_820002A0__ftp_x=1&sbo=0&ne=21 "Birth Registration details"] ''Ancestry.co.uk''</ref> | birth_date = {{Birth date|1964|2|8|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Northampton]], England, UK | death_date = {{Death date and age|2002|12|20|1964|02|08|df=y}} | death_place = London, England, UK | othername = | occupation = Actress | years_active = 1982–2002 | spouse = | domesticpartner = | website = | academyawards = | afiawards = | arielaward = | baftaawards = | bfjaawards = | cesarawards = | emmyawards = | filmfareawards = | geminiawards = | goldencalfawards = | goldenglobeawards = | goldenraspberryawards = | goyaawards = | grammyawards = | iftaawards = | laurenceolivierawards = | naacpimageawards = | nationalfilmawards = | sagawards = | tonyawards = | awards = }}
'''Joanne Campbell''' (8 February 1964 – 20 December 2002) was a British actress and drama therapist best known for playing Liz in the 1980s sitcom ''[[Me and My Girl (TV series)|Me and My Girl]]'' and [[Josephine Baker]] on stage in ''This Is My Dream''.<ref name="Guard090103">Hedley, Philip; [https://www.theguardian.com/news/2003/jan/09/guardianobituaries.arts "Obituary: Joanne Campbell"] ''Guardian.co.uk'', 9 January 2003</ref><ref name="Ind080103">[[Stephen Bourne (writer)|Bourne, Stephen]]; [https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/joanne-campbell-138350.html "Obituary — Joanne Campbell: Actress capable of dazzling stage performances"], ''[[The Independent]]'', 8 January 2003</ref>
==Career== Born in [[Northampton]],<ref name="Guard090103"/> Campbell began her acting career at the [[Theatre Royal, Stratford|Theatre Royal]] in [[Stratford, London|Stratford]], east London, in the 1980s, where she became the first black [[principal boy]] in pantomime. After several other on stage acting roles, she was one of the founding members of the BiBi Crew, the first company made up entirely of black actresses, and co-wrote and acted in several plays for the company. As well as the above-mentioned comedies, her other television roles included parts in ''[[Dramarama (TV series)|Dramarama]]'', ''[[The Bill]]'', ''[[Birds of a Feather]]'' and ''[[Bodger and Badger]]''.
==Death== Campbell died suddenly as a result of [[deep-vein thrombosis]] aged 38 in London in 2002. At the time of her death she was working on the new [[BBC]] children's show ''U Get Me''.<ref name="Guard090103"/><ref name="Ind080103"/>
