{{Infobox person |name = Katherine Chappell |image = |imahe_size = |caption = |birth_name = |birth_date = {{birth date|1985|12|19}} |birth_place = [[Rye (town), New York|Rye, New York]], [[United States]] |death_date = {{death date and age|2015|6|1|1985|12|19}} |death_place = [[Lion Park]], [[Gauteng]], [[South Africa]] |death_cause = Lion attack |other_names = |spouse = |children = |occupation = Visual effects editor }} '''Katherine "Kate" Chappell''' (December 19, 1985 – June 1, 2015) was an American film visual effects editor who worked on ''[[Game of Thrones]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/06/03/game-of-thrones-editor-mauled-lion_n_7501402.html|title='Game Of Thrones' Editor, Katherine Chappell, Mauled To Death By Lion In Tragic Accident|work=The Huffington Post | date=3 June 2015}}</ref> On June 1, 2015, she died after being attacked by a lioness in [[Johannesburg]].
==Biography== Chappell was born on December 19, 1985. She lived with her parents, Jonathan and Mary Elaine Chappell, two sisters and a brother in [[Westchester County]], New York.<ref name="Kate">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3108323/American-woman-29-killed-lion-identified-emerges-taking-pictures-seconds-animal-attacked.html|title=Game of Thrones editor Katherine Chappell mauled to death at Lion Park pictured - Daily Mail Online|work=Mail Online | location=London|date=2 June 2015}}</ref> She graduated from [[Hofstra University]] in [[Long Island]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/south-africa-lion-park-death-5812685|title=South Africa Lion Park death: American tourist killed by predator identified as 29-year-old wildlife conservationist|author=Sam Webb|date=3 June 2015|work=mirror}}</ref> Chappell had lived in [[Vancouver]] since 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/3907059/katherine-chappell-south-africa-lion-attack-victim/|title=Lion Attack Victim Katherine Chappell Worked on 'Game of Thrones'|author=Henry Austin and Katy Tur/NBC News|work=TIME.com|date=3 June 2015}}</ref> She was a visual effects editor of ''Game of Thrones, [[The Secret Life of Walter Mitty (2013 film)|The Secret Life of Walter Mitty]], [[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]], [[Divergent (film)|Divergent]]'', and [[Godzilla (2014 film)|''Godzilla'']].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/game-of-thrones-editor-katherine-chappell-mauled-to-death-by-lion-201536|title=Game of Thrones Editor Katherine Chappell Mauled to Death By Lion - Us Weekly|date=3 June 2015|work=usmagazine.com}}</ref> Chappell was on the team that won a [[Primetime Emmy Award]] for the episode "[[The Children (Game of Thrones)|The Children]]" in the fourth season of ''[[Game of Thrones]]''.<ref name=Huff-Snowdon>{{cite news|last1=Snowdon|first1=Kathryn|title=Game Of Thrones Editor, Katherine Chappell, Mauled To Death By A Lion At South African Safari Park|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/06/03/katherine-chappell-killed-by-lion-game-of-thrones_n_7500120.html|accessdate=3 June 2015|publisher=The Huffington Post|date=3 June 2015}}</ref>
==Death== On June 1, 2015, Chappell was visiting Johannesburg's [[Lion Park]] when a lion lunged through the window of her vehicle, which she had opened to lean out and take photographs, against park rules, and bit her on the neck. Chappell died in Lion Park of her wounds before the paramedics arrived.<ref name="Kate"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bostonherald.com/entertainment/television/television_news/2015/06/game_of_thrones_editor_killed_by_lion_in_south|title='Game of Thrones' editor killed by lion in South Africa|author=Variety Staff|work=bostonherald.com}}</ref> Chappell was visiting South Africa to work on the conservation of wildlife,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Eleftheriou-Smith|first1=Loulla-Mae|title=Katherine Chappell: American woman killed by lion worked for Game of Thrones and wanted to 'protect wildlife'|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/american-woman-killed-by-lion-named-as-katherine-chappell-who-travelled-to-south-africa-on-a-volunteer-mission-to-protect-wildlife-10293523.html|accessdate=3 June 2015|publisher=The Independent|date=3 June 2015|location=London}}</ref> and was raising funds for [[Wildlife ACT]], a conservation charity.<ref name=Huff-Snowdon />
