{{Infobox person | name = Nshan Beshiktashlian | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1898 | birth_place = [[Istanbul]], [[Ottoman Empire]] | death_date = {{Death year and age|1972|1898}} | death_place = [[Paris]], [[France]] | death_cause = | nationality = [[Armenia]]n{{fact|date=May 2018}} | occupation = poet, writer, satirist, and novelist | years_active = | partner = | children = }}
'''Nshan Beshiktashlian''' ({{lang-hy|Նշան Պէշիկթաշլեան}}, born in [[Istanbul]], [[Ottoman Empire]], 1898 - died [[Paris]], [[France]], 1972) was an [[Armenia]]n poet, writer, satirist, and novelist.<ref name="Hacikyan">{{cite book|last=Hacikyan|first=Agop|title=The Heritage of Armenian Literature Volume III: From the Eighteenth Century to Modern Times|year=2005|publisher=Wayne State University Press|location=Detroit, MI|isbn=0-8143-2815-6|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GmtPLvnrc38C&dq=heritage+of+armenian+literature&source=gbs_navlinks_s|author2=Gabriel Basmajian |author3=Edward S. Franchuk |editor=Nourhan Ouzounian|accessdate=19 September 2012|pages=984}}</ref>
== Biography == Nshan Beshiktashlian was born in Istanbul and left at an early age. Due to his abrupt leave, he was forced to leave school at an early age. However, he began to write at 12 years old with his satirical style of writing. He left [[Istanbul]] and continued his writing career in [[Paris]], [[France]] where he remained until his death in 1972.<ref name="Hacikyan"/>
